&lt;p&gt;At Gong, you will join a company built on innovative products, ambitious goals, and passionate people. We are shaping the future of revenue intelligence and we want people who are excited to build what comes next. You will work with a team that dreams big, moves fast, and cares deeply about the craft and about each other. Here, transparency and trust are core to how we operate, and every person has the opportunity to make a visible impact. If you want to grow, stretch, and do work that truly matters, Gong is the place to do the best work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;As a Frontend Engineer at Gong, you will...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a major part of Gong&#39;s Frontend guild with Frontend developers from all the teams in the company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tackle hard technical problems—some at the architecture level, some at the code level, some at the product level—and come up with solutions, balancing practicality and innovation, short and long term.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be the owner of the features you develop, while collaborating with product and UX teams from thinking and wireframes processes to production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be part of our known architecture huddles when we make future decisions about our code and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Constantly learn new things - join professional lectures and workshops organized by Gong. In addition, each developer gets extra learning time on behalf of Gong to gain or improve new professional skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a part of a successful startup technology team that translates our vision into a solid SaaS product that performs, scales, is easy to use, and makes a big impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should apply if you are...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A software engineer between 3-5 years of industry experience developing web applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Someone who enjoys having responsibility and a sense of ownership of the product you are creating.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deeply knowledgeable of how JavaScript works and experienced with React &lt;strong&gt;(a must!)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with backend languages such as Java, Node.js, C#, and others is an advantage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced with large scale, cloud-based web applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience in the architecture of design systems and components.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preferably someone with a degree in computer science or similar discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An all-around player, fast-learner and self-motivated individual.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An excellent communicator and team player, with strong verbal and written skills in English.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Most importantly, a person who enjoys working independently and within a team of highly skilled peers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What makes Engineering at Gong unique?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here at Gong, we trust and empower our employees with ownership to solve complex problems, make the right decisions, and build the best products that create radical impact. We call this “Own. Solve. Impact.” For our engineers, it means it&#39;s not just about writing code. You are involved and able to influence the entire process to create the best product. If you are curious to discover Gong&#39;s wonderful and challenging world, what are you waiting for? Don’t delay - fill in your application details. Who knows, maybe there’s a Gongster in you!&lt;/p&gt;
